# Mobile Brand Context

The "mobile brand" refers to the `/brand` route when viewed on a mobile device (viewport < 600px).

## Key Details

- Route: `/brand` (see `src/App.tsx`)
- Mobile detection: `useIsMobile` hook from `@/hooks/useIsMobile` (breakpoint: 600px)
- Entry point: `src/pages/home/Brand/index.tsx` ‚Äî branches to `MobileBrand` when `isMobile` is true
- Navigation: Users reach `/brand` via More menu (`/more` ‚Üí Brand item)
- View switching: `?view=` URL param (default: `brand-templates`), managed via `useSearchParams`

## Mobile-Specific Components

- `MobileBrand` (`src/pages/home/Brand/MobileBrand.tsx`) ‚Äî full mobile brand page with custom header, gradient banner, brand navigation sheet, and brand templates grid
- `MobileBrand.module.css` ‚Äî styles including fixed header, scroll behavior, back button, action buttons, sheet styles
- `DesignCard` (`src/pages/home/components/CardThumbnails/`) ‚Äî 2-column grid cards for brand template items
- `MobileSearchBox` (`src/pages/home/components/MobileSearchBox/`) ‚Äî search input for brand templates
- `GradientBanner` (`src/shared_components/GradientBanner/`) ‚Äî shared gradient background behind content

## Layout & Behaviour on Mobile

- The page has its **own custom header** (not `MobilePageLayout` or `MobileHomeHeader`), with:
  - Fixed back button (top left, navigates to `/more`)
  - Current view title (appears on scroll)
  - Action buttons (print photo book, more options) at top right
  - White header background that fades in on scroll via `data-mobile-scroll-container` scroll listener
- Content scrolls in a full-height container with `overflow-y: auto`
- Below the gradient banner, the title has a **chevron dropdown button** that opens a brand navigation Sheet
- A search box (`MobileSearchBox`) for searching brand templates
- Templates are organized in sections: **Starred for team** and **All Brand Templates**
- Each section uses a 2-column `Grid` with `DesignCard` components (variant="icon")
- The default landing view is "All Brand Templates" (matching the desktop default)

## Brand Navigation Sheet

- Uses Easel `Sheet` component (`@canva/easel/surface/sheet`) with `size="large"`
- Opened by tapping the chevron next to the page title
- Contains a scrollable menu with all brand views:
  - **All Brand Templates** (highlighted when selected, with `ContentBrandIcon`)
  - **Brand Kit** section: "Canva Brand Kit" with chevron (links to `all-assets`)
  - Top-level: All assets, Guidelines
  - **Core Brand**: Emojis, Logos, Photography, Colors, Fonts, Motion, UI, Visual Suite, Brand voice, Charts
  - **Internal Brand**: Stickers, Canva Values, Script Marks, Canva Photos
- Selected item shows bold text
- Selecting a view updates the `?view=` URL param and closes the sheet

## Key Patterns

- Scroll-based header reveal: attaches scroll listener to `[data-mobile-scroll-container="true"]` element
- Fixed positioning for header elements (z-index 100‚Äì101)
- Header height: `calc(baseUnit * 8)` (64px)
- The `MobileBrand` component does **not** use `MobilePageLayout` ‚Äî it has a fully custom layout
- View labels managed via `viewLabels` Record mapping view keys to display names

## Shared Dependencies

- `src/shared_components/GradientBanner` ‚Äî gradient background
- `src/shared_components/icons` ‚Äî ContentBrandIcon
- `src/pages/home/components/CardThumbnails` ‚Äî DesignCard, ProjectDesign type
- `src/pages/home/components/MobileSearchBox` ‚Äî search input
- `react-router-dom` ‚Äî useNavigate, useSearchParams

## Guidelines

- Always test brand changes against mobile viewport (390x844, or any width < 600px).
- Navigate to `/brand` via More menu on mobile, or directly via URL.
- Prefer touch-friendly controls and adequate tap targets.
- Keep the custom scroll-based header pattern when modifying the layout.
- Brand template data is currently hardcoded in `MobileBrand.tsx` ‚Äî keep in sync with `BrandTemplatesView.tsx` if needed.
- Reuse `DesignCard` from `CardThumbnails` for consistency with other mobile pages.
- Use the `viewLabels` Record when adding new views to keep labels consistent.
